                Online Event
        </div></div><div class="spancol-1-3 card__details-container"><h2 class="card__heading">The dark matters with Chamkaur Ghag</h2><div class="card__description"><p class="event__location">Online event - The Cosmos Series</p><p class="event__date">24 June 2021</p><p class="event__description"><p class="MsoNormal">Dark matter is holding galaxies like our own together, even streaming through our bodies right now, but we know very little about what it is. Understanding the nature of the mysterious dark matter is one of the most important scientific missions of our time.</p><p class="MsoNormal">In this talk <strong>Chamkaur Ghag</strong> will take you to the frontiers of astroparticle physics research to explore searches for dark matter in deep underground laboratories; annihilations in space; signatures in particle colliders, and hints from quantum sensors. We may be on the verge of discovery that will propel us into the dark!</p></p></div><a href="/science-events/dark-matters/" class="card__button button-sub">Find out more</a></div><a href="/science-events/dark-matters/" class="card__link"></a></div></div>                    </div>
                                    
    


    
    
