            width="1200"
        height="800"
    
        /></div><h2 class="card__heading">The Gene Therapy Revolution in Healthcare</h2><a href="/science-events/gene-therapy-revolution/" class="card__link"></a><div class="card__description"><p class="event__location">Free online event</p><p class="event__date">29 July 2021</p><p class="event__description"><p><strong>Gene therapy</strong> is set to revolutionise medicine. The ability to replace the function of a missing or faulty gene offers millions of people with life-threatening, rare conditions, the potential for longer, healthier lives. In some cases, a single one-time treatment can provide a lifetime of benefits.</p><p>This <strong>New Scientist debate</strong> will evaluate how best to assess the value of gene therapies to benefit individuals, healthcare systems as well as broader society. At the forefront of this issue is how healthcare systems and policymakers can prepare for a new era of medicine in a way that gives patients and their families the best outcome.</p></p></div></div><a href="/science-events/gene-therapy-revolution/" class="card__button button-sub">Find out more</a><div class="card__eyebrow card__eyebrow--sponsored-event">
