        As the death toll from<strong> covid-19</strong> rises, discover how researchers around the world are racing to understand the virus and prevent future outbreaks. What are the origins of <strong>coronaviruses</strong>? How are past outbreaks, such as <strong>SARS,</strong><strong>MERS</strong> and <strong>H1N1</strong>, helping us tackle this pandemic? What are we learning about the biology of covid-19 and how it infects human cells? When will we have a vaccine?</p><p>Join <em>New Scientist</em> for a streamed video of our recent <strong>online panel discussion</strong> into the work of scientists. Find out why, despite the grave situation we face, science offers much hope.
